>
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="tagline">Identity over credentials.</p>

  <h2>The core thing</h2>
  <p>
    I need a problem to solve. Not in a dramatic way — it's just how my brain is wired.
    If there's friction, I remove it. If there's a system that could be better, I rebuild it.
    If there's no tool for the job, I make one. This isn't work ethic. It's compulsion.
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm an <strong>INFJ-A</strong> with CliftonStrengths in Strategic, Futuristic, Ideation,
    Intellection, and Command. I think in patterns and systems. I see the shape of things
    before they exist. And I have the follow-through to build them.
  </p>

  <h2>How I think</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Software 3.0:</strong> Prompt > Code. Headless > UI. The interface is the
    intelligence, not the chrome around it. I build for the API first, the agent second,
    the human third.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Passive systems:</strong> You're already generating the signal. We just listen.
    The best systems don't ask you to change your behavior — they observe, learn, and act.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Data sovereignty:</strong> Your data is your data. I build systems that keep
    you in control. Centralized platforms that monetize attention are a dead end.
  </p>

  <h2>The path</h2>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Army EOD</h3>
    <p>Bomb disposal. The ultimate "don't fuck this up" environment. Taught me precision under pressure and how to stay calm when everything is on fire.</p>
    <div class="meta">2009 – 2013</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Site Reliability Engineering — HCA Healthcare</h3>
    <p>Kept critical healthcare infrastructure running at scale. Incident response, automation, the art of keeping systems alive when they want to die.</p>
    <div class="meta">2018 – 2022</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Golden Bear — Founder</h3>
    <p>Built and sold a company. Full stack: product, sales, ops, everything. Learned that building the thing is the easy part — finding the right thing to build is the hard part.</p>
    <div class="meta">2022 – 2024</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Bolt Farm Treehouse — BoltOS</h3>
    <p>AI agent systems. Memory, orchestration, tooling, deployment. Building the infrastructure layer for autonomous AI. This is the most interesting problem I've ever worked on.</p>
    <div class="meta">2025 – present</div>
  </div>

  <h2>Personal</h2>
  <p>
    Married to <strong>Anna</strong> since October 2024. Our son <strong>Lincoln</strong>
    was born November 2024. Fraternal twin. Born June 21, 1991. Lebanon/Nashville, TN.
  </p>
  <p>
    Orthodox Christian + Zen/Dao. The contemplative and the practical aren't in conflict —
    they're the same thing viewed from different angles.
  </p>
  <p>
    I read constantly. Research papers, philosophy, systems thinking, whatever's sharp.
    I think best out loud and build best alone.
  </p>

  <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
  <p>
    Director-level AI leadership. The right team, the right mission, the right amount of
    chaos. I want to build something that matters with people who are serious about it.
  </p>
  <p>
    Or — founding something new. If the right cofounder appeared tomorrow, I'd have a
    conversation.
  </p>
